{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μακράν</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> <b>μακρήν</b>, <i>accusative</i> <i>feminine</i> of μακρός used as <i>adverb</i>, <b>far</b>, μ. ἀνωτέρω θακῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 314 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; μ. λελειμμένος left <b>far</b> behind,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 857; οὐδέπω μακρὰν πτέσθαι σθένοντες 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 16; ἀπελθεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 438 (Lyric poetry); ἱέναι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.17; ἔστ᾽ οὐ μ. ἄπωθεν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1184 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοὔργον οὐ μ. λέγεις the business you speak of is not <b>far</b> to seek, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 26 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i>, <b>far from</b>, βαρβάρου χθονός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Taurica” 629; κἂν ᾖ τοῦ γένους μ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 192; τῶν πολεμίων 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.50.8; οὐ μ. ἀπό τινος [prev. author] 3.45.2: in _comparative_, ἀποσκίδνασθαι μακροτέραν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>to a greater distance</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.98; πορεύεσθαι μ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.2.11: _superlative_, ὅτι μακροτάτην\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>as far as possible</b>, with <i>genitive</i> loci, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 7.8.20. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> μακρὰν λέγειν speak <b>at length</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 713, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1259; μ. τείνειν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1296, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1040; ἐκτείνειν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 916. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of Time, <b>long</b>, μ. ζῆν, ἀναμένειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 323, 1389 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ μ. <b>shortly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 850, etc.; so οὐκ ἐς μακρήν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.108, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 925, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 454, etc.; εὐθύς, οὐκ εἰς μὰκράν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] (but, not <b>at length</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “de Pietate - Herkulanische Studien” 25). \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3112","accentedUnicode":"μακράν","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3117","matchingForm":"μακρός","stepTransliteration":"makros","gloss":"long/distant","_zh_tw_Gloss":"很長","_es_Gloss":"largo/distante","_zh_Gloss":"很长"}],"shortDef":"far away, distant, long way off","mediumDef":"far away, distant, long way off <br /><b>far, far off, at a distance, far distant, a long way off</b> <ref='Mat.8.30'>Mt. 8:30</ref>; <ref='Mrk.12.34'>Mk. 12:34</ref>; <i>metaphorically</i> <greek>οἱ μακράν</greek>, <b>remote, alien,</b> <ref='Eph.2.13, 17'>Eph. 2:13, 17</ref>; so <greek>οἱ εἰς μακράν</greek>, <ref='Act.2.39'>Acts 2:39</ref>","stepGloss":"far","stepTransliteration":"makran","count":0,"_es_Definition":"en la distancia, remoto ; lejos (HCH.2:39)","_zh_tw_Definition":"遙遠的, 遠距離的","_zh_Definition":"遥远的, 远距离的","_step_Type":"word","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"meaning\",\"G3117\",\"long/distant\",15,\"μακρός\"],[\"in the form\",\"G3112\",\"far\",0,\"μακράν\"]]","_vi_Definition":"xa khỏi; xa; một con đường dài","_zh_tw_Gloss":"遠","_es_Gloss":"lejos","_zh_Gloss":"远"}]}